.TH "SVGANIMATEDSTRING" "3JS" "January 6, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
SVGAnimatedString \- SVGAnimatedString
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]SVGAnimatedString\f[B]\f[R] interface represents string
attributes which can be animated from each SVG declaration.
You need to create SVG attribute before doing anything else, everything
should be declared inside this.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]SVGAnimatedString.animVal\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A string representing the animated value of the reflected attribute
value.
If the given attribute is not currently being animated, it contains the
same value as \f[CR]baseVal\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]SVGAnimatedString.baseVal\f[R]
A string representing the base value of the reflected attribute before
applying any animations.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
\f[I]The \f[CI]SVGAnimatedString\f[I] interface do not provide any
specific methods.\f[R]
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]SVGScriptElement.href\f[R], an object of this type.
